Program: Discovery
Title: Lost Continents - India
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jry0d
Last Broadcast Date: 21 January 2002
How the subcontinent was formed - the story of the Indian land mass. How the movement of the tectonic plates over thousands of kilometres caused a collision that changed the climate and plunged a whole continent into the ocean; it also helped create the planet's tallest mountain range.